# Privileged fetch user errors

When extension UI surfaces errors from **`privilegedExtensionFetch*`** (background `runtime.sendMessage` fetch), **never** show raw allowlist strings such as **`URL not allowlisted for privileged fetch.`** or **`URL is not allowlisted for privileged extension fetch.`** to users.

## User-facing resolver

- Use **`resolvePrivilegedFetchUserMessage`** in [`apps/extension/lib/privileged-fetch-user-message.ts`](../../apps/extension/lib/privileged-fetch-user-message.ts).
- Prefer **`PrivilegedFetchUserError`** ([`apps/extension/components/privileged-fetch-user-error.tsx`](../../apps/extension/components/privileged-fetch-user-error.tsx)) or **`PrivilegedFetchErrorPanel`** for full error panels with Retry.
- **`ExtensionReloadHint`** ([`apps/extension/components/extension-reload-hint.tsx`](../../apps/extension/components/extension-reload-hint.tsx)) must accompany allowlist and background-unavailable cases — it links to the browser extensions page with reload steps.

## When adding a new HTTPS host

1. Append the hostname to **`PRIVILEGED_EXTENSION_FETCH_ALLOWED_HOSTS`** in [`apps/extension/lib/privileged-extension-fetch.ts`](../../apps/extension/lib/privileged-extension-fetch.ts).
2. Add matching **`host_permissions`** in [`apps/extension/wxt.config.ts`](../../apps/extension/wxt.config.ts).
3. Rebuild and reload the unpacked extension (or ship an update) — users with a stale service worker see the allowlist message until reload.

## Copy rules

- **Allowlist / background unavailable:** plain-language reload instructions only; no internal error text.
- **User-actionable errors** (API key, rate limit, network, settings path): show the formatted message as-is.
- **Other opaque internals:** generic “could not load” copy; optional small monospace technical line only when it helps support — not for allowlist cases.

## Tests

Extend [`apps/extension/lib/privileged-fetch-user-message.test.ts`](../../apps/extension/lib/privileged-fetch-user-message.test.ts) when adding new mapped error classes.
